1. version choose
	lxc-0.7.0 
	kernel 
--------tips
if try to install lxc-0.8.0, the apparmor will be needed. 
for current version of kernel, incompatible things occurs.
apparmor-2.7.2.tar.gz
apparmor-2.8.1.tar.gz
	
	
2. kernel update via yum 
[root@node4 ~]# uname -r
2.6.32-220.el6.x86_64
[root@node4 ~]# cat /etc/redhat-release
Red Hat Enterprise Linux Server release 6.2 (Santiago)

	yum search kernel
	yum install kernel kernel-devel

-------------
after updating,  you will see two kernel images under /boot 
-------------
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root   100943 Nov  9  2011 config-2.6.32-220.el6.x86_64
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root   104085 Mar 13 08:51 config-2.6.32-358.2.1.el6.x86_64
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 15884257 May 13  2012 initramfs-2.6.32-220.el6.x86_64.img
-rw-r--r--. 1 root root 16336993 Mar 22 17:38 initramfs-2.6.32-358.2.1.el6.x86_64.img
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 root root  3938800 Nov  9  2011 vmlinuz-2.6.32-220.el6.x86_64
-rwxr-xr-x. 1 root root  4043920 Mar 13 08:51 vmlinuz-2.6.32-358.2.1.el6.x86_64
-----------
